It was written in 1970 in Woodstock and was the main track off the duo's 1972 album, Summer Breeze. The song helped the album sell two million copies in the US. Seals and Crofts played live to audiences of 12,000, with many coming along just to hear their hit song. James Seals was born in Texas in 1942 and started playing the violin aged six. Both Seals and Crofts played in a group called The Champs which had a No.1 hit with Tequila. In the late 1960s they formed a duo in the mould of Simon and Garfunkel but struggled until Summer Breeze came along. Jim Seals born October 17, 1941, died June 5, 2022, aged 80 